A group led by New York investorAsher Edelman said Morse Shoe Inc agreed to provide itconfidential company information and that his group would makean offer to buy Morse only in a friendly, negotiated deal.    The group also said in a filing with the Securities andExchange Commission that its members would not, without Morseapproval, buy or offer to buy any company securities giving thegroup a 10 pct or more stake in the company.    Edelman and his group said his terms held until the earlierof 90 days from March 3 or the date on which Morse announces adefinite agreement for its sale.    At the same time, the Edelman group said it cut its stakein Morse to 8.4 pct from 9.7 pct. Reuter&#3;